250 g Mild Italian Sausage, uncased
170 g Spaghetti
113 g Mirepoix
56 g Spring Mix
7 g Thyme
½ cup Marinara Sauce
56 mL Cream
¼ cup Parmesan Cheese, shredded
1 tbsp Chicken Stock Powder
1 tbsp Red Wine Vinegar
½ tsp Sugar*
1 tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Pepper*
0.13 tsp Salt*
2 tbsp Unsalted Butter*

Strip thyme leaves from stems, then roughly chop.
Add vinegar, 1/2 tsp (1 tsp) sugar and 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil to a large bowl. Stir to combine. Add spring mix. Do not mix until step 5.

Add spaghetti to the boiling water. Cook uncovered, stirring occasionally, until tender, 10-12 min.
Reserve 1/2 cup (1 cup) pasta water.
When pasta is done, drain and return spaghetti to the same pot, off heat.

Meanwhile, heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat.
When hot, add 2 tbsp (4 tbsp) butter, then mirepoix, Italian sausage and thyme. Season with salt and pepper.
Cook, breaking up Italian sausage into small pieces, until no pink remains, 4-5 min.**

Add marinara sauce, stock powder, cream and 1/4 cup (1/2 cup) reserved pasta water to the pan with Italian sausage.
Bring to a boil.
Once boiling, reduce heat to medium-low. Cook, stirring occasionally, until sauce thickens slightly, 4-5 min.

Add bolognese sauce to the pot with spaghetti, then toss to coat. ( TIP: For a lighter sauce consistency, add more reserved pasta water, 1-2 tbsp at a time, if desired.)
Toss salad.
Divide spaghetti bolognese and salad between plates.
Sprinkle Parmesan over top.

If you've opted to get Italian sausage, cook it in the same way the recipe instructs you to cook the ground pork.